[SN]TITLE[SN]
Two rescued from Cromarty Firth after microlight ditches

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Two people have been rescued after their microlight aircraft ditched in the Cromarty Firth.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The coastguard service was alerted to the incident, just west of Invergordon, at about 14:15.
The RNLI lifeboat from Invergordon was launched and managed to recover the casualties. They were later winched on board a coastguard helicopter and taken to Raigmore Hospital in Inverness.
It is understood that their injuries are not life-threatening.
